cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CL

This paper is primarily focused on computer vision tasks, specifically image classification and object detection. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also introduces a novel self-attention mechanism, which is a recent advance in natural language processing and has been applied to sequence modeling and generative modeling tasks. This suggests that cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are also likely sub-categories. Additionally, the paper proposes to augment convolutional operators with self-attention, which involves modifying the architecture of neural networks. This suggests that cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper involves language processing tasks such as image captioning, which suggests that cs.CL (Computation and Language) is a less likely but still possible sub-category.
